20 defuisse] as HM. point out, this remark seems to imply that Antony had charged Cicero with writing verses to the neglect of other more important duties.

21 omni genere monumentorum] Cicero refers chiefly to his philosophical and rhetorical writings. His desire to be of use to the youth of his country by promoting the study of literature and philosophy is a marked and honourable feature in his character.

28 scalas tabernae librariae] ‘the staircase of a bookshop’. Whole houses in Rome were often let in portions for shop poemises, each tradesman hiring so much of the house as he required for the purposes of his trade.
